    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Setting an Example</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Fred A Rosenberg letter on August 8 photo of scientist examining possible West Nile virus-carrying mosquitoes without gloves and with Band-aid covering cut on his finger; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What kind of an example is it to my medical microbiology students when they see the photograph with ''Clues to an Alien Virus'' (Aug. 8), showing a scientist manipulating mosquitoes which presumably may be carriers of the West Nile virus without gloves and with a Band-Aid covering a cut or other wound on his finger?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What kind of an example is it to my medical microbiology students when they see the photograph with ''Clues to an Alien Virus'' (Aug. 8), showing a scientist manipulating mosquitoes which presumably may be carriers of the West Nile virus without gloves and with a Band-Aid covering a cut or other wound on his finger?</p>
        <p>The use of tweezers is not an excuse.</p>
        <p>Accidents do happen.</p>
        <p>DR. FRED A. ROSENBERG  Thousand Oaks, Calif.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
